BiOMOTUM Skip to content Home Technology About Contact Login Home Technology About Contact energize every step Transforming the treatment of movement disorders with intelligent, wearable At BiOMOTUM We envision a world where children and adults with movement challenges lead healthy, productive and socially satisfying Million million people in the US have a physical disability that limits their mobility, negatively impacting their Many of these individuals are unable to walk unassisted or go up and down At BiOMOTUM, we are focused on improving mobility outcomes in children and adults with movement Our wearable rehabilitation robots provide mobility enhancement ‚Äì transforming rehabilitation and improving The Current Solution Physical Therapy Physical Therapy (PT) is essential for treating movement disorders and there is a strong relationship between the amount of therapy and improvements in Insufficient Dose Unfortunately, most individuals do not receive enough PT and the delivery of PT can be inefficient, limiting the dose and positive changes in There is currently no viable way to provide a sufficient dose of active gait training that will lead to improvements in Our Solution A lightweight, wearable, powered device for gait training Increased therapy dose better mobility Greater independence positive Community engaging & informative Introducing our Robotic Ankle Assist Device The RA 2 D Get Get Assist & Go Ultra light powered assistance Works everywhere Targeted neuro rehab Get stronger Why RA 2 D? Low Cost Innovative, elegant design Common motors drives Go Anywhere Robust controls Variable terrain and stairs Connected Mobility data User community Ground Breaking Results Taken at the beginning and end of a week for intervention, these videos show the benefit of using the RA 2 D in Note the increase in walking speed and improved The child is not using the RA 2 D in these 0 % Faster walking speeds Able to keep up 0 % Better walking efficiency Makes walking easier 1 % Better Muscle Control Improved function Innovative Technology 0 lb Total Weight Lightest device available $ 1 k Federal Funding capital NIH & NSF 1 Patents Utility Patents Pending User Testomonials I feel like superman! yr old with cerebral palsy This is for our Mom of child with cerebral palsy I can already tell this would help me walk and stay active! yr old with parkinson s disease About Us History Zach Lerner and Ray Browning met in at Colorado State Since that time, Zach and Ray have been focused on understanding and optimizing pediatric As former elite athletes, they both have a passion for movement and the vision that all individuals have physical experiences that allow them to see and achieve their Over the last several years, Zach has created robotic assistive devices that offer a lightweight, portable and effective way to improve mobility in children with Cerebral These devices are the foundation for Today Our mission is to improve mobility and rehabilitation outcomes in individuals with movement We aim to accomplish this mission by leveraging a design approach, gathering insight from affected individuals and clinicians, to create, produce and distribute intelligent, holistic and engaging wearable Our technology is built on a foundation of rigorous clinical Our systems are designed to improve neuromuscular function and quality of life across the We have a functional device that has proven mobility Tomorrow At BiOMOTUM, we believe that robotic assistive devices are a key partner in neuromuscular These devices will allow mobility assistance and therapy to be delivered anywhere, This, in turn, should accelerate the neural plasticity that facilitates lasting improvements in function and Our robotic ankle assist device is just the first step toward our vision of a world where children and adults with movement disorders lead healthy, productive and socially satisfying Welcome to a New Era   General 1 ‚Äî Psilera Bioscience 0 Team Current Page: Research Contact Open Menu Close Menu Team Current Page: Research Contact Natural Products and Mental Health From cultivation and extraction to structure elucidation and synthesis of novel compounds, Psilera Bioscience strives to enhance our understanding of neuromodulators and how they can be used to treat Using innovative cultivation, metabolomics and statistical analysis techniques, we apply natural products drug discovery to the modern Our focus is agonist and antagonistic effects on serotonin receptors (5-HT) and other neurologically relevant proteins to target addiction, depression, neurodegenerative diseases, PTSD, and other burdens to mental health . Our Projects Cultivation Technology Using technology to optimize and regulate the chemistry of fungal Informed Separations Managing the unique and diverse chemistry from nature to remove undesirables and maintain efficient drug discovery Innovative Synthesis Inspired by tryptamines and other natural psychoactives, our compound design aims to enhance Unique Formulations Research and development of new drug delivery systems for optimal patient The Science ‚ÄúWe live by our eyes and ears and tend generally to be oblivious to the chemical happenings in our Such happenings are All organisms engender chemical signals, and all, in their respective ways, respond to the chemical emissions of ‚Äù - Thomas Eisner and Jerrold Meinwald in Chemical Ecology (1995) Natural Products From antibiotics like penicillin and erythromycin to cancer therapeutics like taxol, natural products have served as templates for drug discovery since its Catechins in green tea, cannabinoids from cannabis, and fungal indoles are all for their medical and general health These compounds all fall into the realm of ‚Äúnatural products‚Äù, which are chemicals created by natural substances like plants, fungi, and even marine Some can be medically beneficial as mentioned above, while others can have detrimental outcomes like toxins and Many of these chemicals are used for ecological roles to protect organisms from predators or even attract Their inherent capability to bind to biological receptors in nature make them perfect candidates for drug discovery targeting the human body and When researched thoroughly and guided by natural products chemists and pharmacologists, these compounds can lead to novel therapeutics in our inherent battles against mental illness, aging, cancers, infectious disease, and overall Literature Review Mental Health & Cognition Mental illness has been named the leading burden on society by The Lancet Psychiatry .
